##Sales Analysis Dashboard (Power BI)
 ##Project Overview

This project presents an interactive Power BI dashboard for analyzing sales performance using the AdventureWorks dataset.
The dashboard provides deep insights into sales, customers, products, territories, and returns, following a star schema data model and best practices in Power BI.

## Objectives

Analyze total sales, quantities, and returns.

Understand customer behavior and demographics.

Evaluate product performance across categories and subcategories.

Compare sales and returns by country and territory.

Measure operational metrics such as Lead Time (LTD).

## Dataset

The project uses multiple CSV files from the AdventureWorks dataset, including:

Fact Tables

FACT_Sales

FACT_Returns

Dimension Tables

DIM_Calendar

DIM_Customer

DIM_Product

DIM_Territory

The data model is designed using a Star Schema to ensure optimal performance and accurate filtering.

## Data Model

One-to-many relationships between dimension tables and fact tables.

Separate fact tables for Sales and Returns.

Centralized _Measure table for all DAX measures.

Calendar table used for time intelligence (Year, Quarter, Month).

## Key Measures (DAX)

Some of the key measures implemented in this project include:

Total Sales

Total Quantity

Total Returns ($ & Quantity)

Active Customers

Activation %

Average / Min / Max Lead Time (LTD)

Min / Max / Avg Product Price

Total Customers

Total Products

Number of Territories

